==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zincous
<hw>Zinc"ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Of, pertaining to, or containing,
zinc; zincic; <as>as, <ex>zincous</ex> salts</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Hence, formerly, basic, basylous, as opposed to
<contr>chlorous</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the
positive pole of a galvanic battery; electro-positive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>'zine</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>zine</ent>⟦br⟧
